 <title>A.4.b. Change of Degree Program</title>
 <link>https://www.middlebury.edu/old-about/old-handbook/handbook_archive/handbook-2018-2019/iv.-policies-for-the-institute/a.-academic-policies/a.4.-change-of-academic-program/a.4.b.-change-of-degree-program/node/632397</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;The process for changing degree programs includes the following steps:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;The student discusses the matter with his/her advisor, including eligibility and possible implications for degree requirements and degree completion.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;The advisor directs the student to the appropriate procedure, depending on the studentâ€™s current and future programs. Some changes of degree program require a new application through the admission office.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Once a change of program has been completed and approved by all relevant parties, the advisor works with the student to develop a new plan of study for the new degree.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
